% Chapter 1: Introduction
\chapter{Introduction}
\label{chap:introduction}

\section{Brief Overview of the Project}
Pick My Dish is a comprehensive recipe management application developed using Flutter for the frontend and Node.js for the backend. The application serves as a digital cooking assistant that helps users discover recipes based on various criteria including available ingredients, emotional state, dietary preferences, and time constraints. The system incorporates modern software engineering practices including Scrum methodology, design patterns, and a well-structured architecture.

\section{Problem Statement}
In today's fast-paced world, individuals face several challenges in meal preparation:

\begin{itemize}[leftmargin=*]
    \item \textbf{Decision Fatigue}: Users struggle to decide what to cook daily
    \item \textbf{Ingredient Waste}: People often buy ingredients without specific recipes in mind
    \item \textbf{Time Constraints}: Limited time for meal preparation
    \item \textbf{Emotional Eating}: Food choices often influenced by emotional state
    \item \textbf{Recipe Management}: Difficulty in organizing and finding saved recipes
    \item \textbf{Social Sharing}: Lack of platform to share and discover recipes within a community
\end{itemize}

\section{Objectives and Purpose}

\subsection{Primary Objectives}
\begin{enumerate}
    \item Develop an intelligent recipe recommendation system
    \item Create a user-friendly interface for recipe management
    \item Implement social features for recipe sharing
    \item Provide personalized user experience
    \item Ensure cross-platform compatibility
\end{enumerate}

\subsection{Purpose}
To create a comprehensive solution that simplifies meal planning, reduces food waste, and builds a community of cooking enthusiasts through an intuitive and intelligent platform.

\section{Key Features and Innovations}

\subsection{Core Features}
\begin{table}[H]
\centering
\caption{Core Features of Pick My Dish}
\begin{tabularx}{\textwidth}{|l|X|}
\hline
\textbf{Feature} & \textbf{Description} \\
\hline
Smart Recipe Discovery & Mood-based filtering, ingredient matching, time-based filtering \\
\hline
Recipe Management & Upload, edit, delete, favorite, categorize recipes \\
\hline
User Management & Registration, authentication, profile management \\
\hline
Social Features & View community recipes, rate and review, share \\
\hline
Advanced Features & Offline storage, image caching, real-time search \\
\hline
\end{tabularx}
\end{table}

\subsection{Innovations}
\begin{enumerate}
    \item \textbf{Emotion-Based Filtering}: First recipe app to incorporate emotional state in recipe recommendations
    \item \textbf{Ingredient Intelligence}: Smart ingredient matching and suggestions
    \item \textbf{Context-Aware Recommendations}: Multi-factor filtering system
    \item \textbf{Progressive Offline Support}: Full functionality with limited connectivity
\end{enumerate}

\section{Target Audience}

\subsection{Primary Users}
\begin{itemize}
    \item Home Cooks: Individuals cooking at home regularly
    \item College Students: Limited cooking facilities and budget
    \item Working Professionals: Time-constrained individuals
    \item Health-Conscious Individuals: People with specific dietary requirements
    \item Cooking Enthusiasts: People who enjoy trying new recipes
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Secondary Users}
\begin{itemize}
    \item Food Bloggers: Content creators sharing recipes
    \item Restaurants: Professional chefs sharing signature dishes
    \item Nutritionists: Professionals recommending healthy recipes
\end{itemize}

